findings.remediation:
Add email format validation using a regex or a library like validator.js:

```typescript
const emailRegex = /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/;
if (!emailRegex.test(email)) {
  return { statusCode: 400, body: JSON.stringify({ error: 'Invalid email format' }) };
}
```

Sanitize input to remove newline characters before using in email headers:

```typescript
const sanitize = (input: string) => input.replace(/[\r\n]/g, '').trim();
const safeName = sanitize(name);
const safeEmail = sanitize(email);
const safeMessage = message.trim();

await transporter.sendMail({
  from: `"Portfolio Contact" <${from}>`,
  to: from,
  replyTo: safeEmail,
  subject: `Contact from ${safeName} (${safeEmail})`,
  text: safeMessage,
  html: `<p><strong>From:</strong> ${safeName} &lt;${safeEmail}&gt;</p><p>${safeMessage.replace(/\n/g, '<br>')}</p>`,
});
```

Remove the detailed 'missing' and 'hint' fields from the error response in production:

```typescript
return {
  statusCode: 500,
  body: JSON.stringify({ error: 'Email service not configured.' }),
};
```

Keep detailed error info only in server-side logs.
